This class builds on the skills learned in Levels 1 and 2. Participants learn to swim the front crawl and elementary backstroke at rudimentary proficiency levels and are introduced to the scissors and dolphin kicks. Participants also learn the rules for headfirst entries and begin to learn to enter the water headfirst from a seated position at poolside (if the water is 9 feet deep or deeper). Discover the serene beauty of San Francisco’s waterways with a self-guided kayaking experience at either Lake Merced or China Basin. Paddle at your own pace as you explore the lake’s tranquil waters, diverse wildlife, and natural habitats—an ideal way to connect with nature and enjoy a refreshing outdoor adventure right in the city. Enrollment includes the rental of a tandem (two-person) kayak and covers up to two participants. Personal flotation devices are provided for all participants. Children 12 and under must be accompanied by an adult in the kayak. All participants must sign a release waiver on the day of their session. Instructional safety videos must be viewed prior to paddling; a link to the videos and waiver will be emailed the week before your scheduled time. Registered participants under the age of 12 must be accompanied on the water by a registered parent or guardian. Expect to get wet—please bring a towel and a change of clothes.

There is much more in Hatha yoga practice than poses. In this series, we still explore practices aimed to improve our physical well-being through asanas (poses); we also introduce practices that include pranayama (breath expansion) techniques, and finally we experience the benefits of simple meditation techniques. The intention is awareness at a physical, mental and emotional level on as well as off the mat.

This class builds on the skills learned in Levels 1 and 2. Participants learn to swim the front crawl and elementary backstroke at rudimentary proficiency levels and are introduced to the scissors and dolphin kicks. Participants learn the survival float and increase the time duration for treading water. Participants also learn the rules for headfirst entries and begin to learn to enter the water headfirst from a seated position at poolside (if the water is 9 feet deep or deeper). On successful completion of Level 3, participants have achieved basic water competency in a pool environment. Prerequisite: Successful completion of Level 2. Children must be 48 to participate.  Registration is limited to one swim class per participant.

event_name: First Steps Excelsior (Playgroup, English, Spanish, Cantonese, Vietnamese)
event_description: Build healthy bonding and enjoy fun activities together, while learning about your child’s cognitive and emotional development. Activities include arts, movement, songs, and stories. For ages 6 – 36 months + parents/caregivers. Free to enroll! Please note: due to our small class size, we ask families to register only for the classes you are able to attend. If you are no longer able to attend a class, please cancel your registration or contact us at firststeps@fccenters.org. Thank you! Registration will open at 9:00 am on the 28th of each month.   ·Portola: Mondays and Wednesdays, 9:00-10:30 am · Excelsior: Tuesdays and Thursdays, 9:00-10:30 am · Visitacion Valley: Thursdays, 9:30-11:00 am. (18-36 months + caregiver) For more information or to join, contact Elsa at 415.715.6746 or firststeps@fccenters.org • • • Primeros Pasos (First Steps) es un espacio para que las familias aprendan juntas. Las maestras lo guiarán a usted y a sus pequeños a través de actividades que incluyen canciones, bailes, y lecturas divertidas. Para edades de 6–36 meses + cuidador/a. Gratis para inscribirse. Tenga en cuenta: debido a nuestro pequeño tamaño de clase, le pedimos a las familias que se registren solo para las clases a las que puede asistir. Si ya no puede asistir a una clase, cancele su registro o contáctenos en firststeps@fccenters.org. ¡Gracias! Las inscripciones se abrirán el día 28 de cada mes a las 9 de la mañana. • • • First Steps是適合孩子和家長一起學習的遊戲小組。 我們的老師將與您們一起歌曲、舞蹈、閲讀等活動。 免費報名。適合6-36個月的孩子 + 家長/監護人。 請注意：由於我們的班級規模較小，我們要求家庭只註冊您可以參加的課程。 如果您不能再上課，請取消註冊或通過 firststeps@fccenters.org 聯繫我們。 謝謝你! 每月28日上午9:00開始報名。 • • • First Steps là một nhóm trẻ mẫu giáo được giám sát bởi người lớn để các gia đình học tập cùng nhau. Các giáo viên của chúng tôi sẽ hướng dẫn bạn và con bạn thông qua các hoạt động hấp dẫn liên quan đến bài hát, điệu nhảy ngộ nghĩnh. Từ 6-36 tháng tuổi + cha mẹ/người chăm sóc. Ghi danh miễn phí. Xin lưu ý: do quy mô lớp học nhỏ, chúng tôi yêu cầu các gia đình chỉ đăng ký cho các lớp học mà bạn có thể tham dự. Nếu bạn không thể tham gia lớp học được nữa, vui lòng hủy đăng ký hoặc liên hệ với chúng tôi tại firststeps@fccenters.org. Cảm ơn! Cổng đăng ký sẽ mở vào lúc 9:00 sáng ngày 28 hàng tháng.

event_name: Exploring Water Based Media in Abstract Landscapes
event_description: When you    think of water based paints, you might only think of watercolor and maybe    acrylic. But the truth is, there are a wide variety of possibilities    including watercolor pencils, water soluble crayons and pastels, ink, and    more. The diversity of mark making and the changeable nature of those marks    offer much to explore. This is a process based class that prioritizes    experimentation as a way to let go of perfectionism. Only happy accidents    here!      We will do several quick studies and then use our favorite ideas and    techniques to make a large work on 350 weight cold press paper. All materials    provided.

event_description: In this    workshop you will learn the basic steps of the trace monotype process. This    easy printing technique is called “trace monotype” because you trace the    desired image on the back of the paper. The act of tracing the image    transfers the ink to the paper, creating a one-of-a-kind print. In this    workshop we will be using non-toxic, water-soluble printing inks. Prints will    be hand-pulled without a press. No previous printing experience is needed.    Materials provided. Discover the serene beauty of San Francisco’s waterways with a self-guided kayaking experience at either Lake Merced or China Basin. Paddle at your own pace as you explore the lake’s tranquil waters, diverse wildlife, and natural habitats—an ideal way to connect with nature and enjoy a refreshing outdoor adventure right in the city. Enrollment includes the rental of a tandem (two-person) kayak and covers up to two participants. Personal flotation devices are provided for all participants. Children 12 and under must be accompanied by an adult in the kayak. All participants must sign a release waiver on the day of their session. Instructional safety videos must be viewed prior to paddling; a link to the videos and waiver will be emailed the week before your scheduled time. Registered participants under the age of 12 must be accompanied on the water by a registered parent or guardian. Expect to get wet—please bring a towel and a change of clothes.

Got a favorite movie? Ever wonder how the great movies got their magic? This class teaches you how! This class is an exploration of cinema style and technique through replication, imitation, creation of cinema, movies, TV, and net series. The class watches and analyzes famous movies, focusing on specific techniques, which they then replicate in class. First we watch it, then we do it! This class will use short scenes, script analysis, making short-films, lighting, camera drills, and students will practice acting/blocking tactics for movie success.

Our after school program is an experience that provides a safe and nurturing environment for youth in grades K-5 to develop life long recreation and leisure skills. Participants will receive homework assistance, be exposed to an environment that will promote literacy, encourage communication and empowerment skills while providing recreation activities that include sports, group games, arts and culture, community exploration and seasonal special events. Parents will have the option to pay the entire fee upon registration. Payment plans are available. $270 is due upon registration and on the first day of October, January and March of the school year.

This class builds on the skills learned in Levels 1 and 2. Participants learn to swim the front crawl and elementary backstroke at rudimentary proficiency levels and are introduced to the scissors and dolphin kicks. Participants learn the survival float and increase the time duration for treading water. Participants also learn the rules for headfirst entries and begin to learn to enter the water headfirst from a seated position at poolside (if the water is 9 feet deep or deeper). On successful completion of Level 3, participants have achieved basic water competency in a pool environment. Prerequisite: Successful completion of Level 2. Children must be 48 to participate.  Registration is limited to one swim class per participant.

This class focuses on helping participants refine their performance of all six swimming strokes (front crawl, back crawl, butterfly, breaststroke, elementary backstroke, and sidestroke). Participants perform these strokes with increased proficiency and can swim them for greater distances. Participants also learn to perform flip turns on the front and back. Prerequisite: Successful completion of Level 4.

event_name: Adult Swim - Improving Skills and Swimming Strokes
event_description: This class seeks to improve participants' proficiency in basic aquatic skills (including rotary breathing, surface dives and treading) and the six basic swimming strokes (i.e., front crawl, back crawl, butterfly, breaststroke, elementary backstroke and sidestroke). (The butterfly stroke is optional.) Participants also learn skills and concepts needed to stay safe around water, in addition to those needed to help themselves or others in an aquatic emergency.

There is much more in Hatha yoga practice than poses. In this series, we still explore practices aimed to improve our physical well-being through asanas (poses); we also introduce practices that include pranayama (breath expansion) techniques, and finally we experience the benefits of simple meditation techniques. The intention is awareness at a physical, mental and emotional level on as well as off the mat.

Playful Intuitive Art Exploration is a fun and exploratory drawing and painting class that gives folks an opportunity to express themselves creatively through creating art and connecting with their intuition.  We will be taking inspiration from unique real-world images (centered around nature and microscopic photography) which incorporate interesting colors, textures, and shapes. You will learn basic drawing techniques using the elements of art and will be experimenting with abstract and representational concepts using your intuition as a guide. You get to be the orchestrator here.  There is no right or wrong in this class and no prior drawing experience is necessary!  Join us and have some fun!

On successful completion of Level 3, participants have achieved basic water competency in a pool environment. Prerequisite: Successful completion of Level 2. Children must be 48 to participate.  Registration is limited to one swim class per participant.

This class builds on the skills learned in Levels 1 and 2. Participants learn to swim the front crawl and elementary backstroke at rudimentary proficiency levels and are introduced to the scissors and dolphin kicks. Participants learn the survival float and increase the time duration for treading water. Participants also learn the rules for headfirst entries and begin to learn to enter the water headfirst from a seated position at poolside (if the water is 9 feet deep or deeper). On successful completion of Level 3, participants have achieved basic water competency in a pool environment. Prerequisite: Successful completion of Level 2. Children must be 48 to participate.  Registration is limited to one swim class per participant.

Discover the serene beauty of San Francisco’s waterways with a self-guided kayaking experience at either Lake Merced or China Basin. Paddle at your own pace as you explore the lake’s tranquil waters, diverse wildlife, and natural habitats—an ideal way to connect with nature and enjoy a refreshing outdoor adventure right in the city. Enrollment includes the rental of a tandem (two-person) kayak and covers up to two participants. Personal flotation devices are provided for all participants. Children 12 and under must be accompanied by an adult in the kayak. All participants must sign a release waiver on the day of their session. Instructional safety videos must be viewed prior to paddling; a link to the videos and waiver will be emailed the week before your scheduled time. Registered participants under the age of 12 must be accompanied on the water by a registered parent or guardian. Expect to get wet—please bring a towel and a change of clothes.

This class builds on the skills learned in Levels 1 and 2. Participants learn to swim the front crawl and elementary backstroke at rudimentary proficiency levels and are introduced to the scissors and dolphin kicks. Participants learn the survival float and increase the time duration for treading water. Participants also learn the rules for headfirst entries and begin to learn to enter the water headfirst from a seated position at poolside (if the water is 9 feet deep or deeper). On successful completion of Level 3, participants have achieved basic water competency in a pool environment. Prerequisite: Successful completion of Level 2. Children must be 48 to participate.  Registration is limited to one swim class per participant.

This class should improve participants' proficiency in performing the swimming strokes that were introduced in Level 3. Participants perform these strokes with increased proficiency and can swim them for greater distances. In addition, participants learn the arm actions that accompany the scissors kick and breaststroke kick to begin performing the sidestroke and breaststroke at rudimentary proficiency levels. Participants also learn the back crawl and butterfly at rudimentary proficiency levels, in addition to the basics of performing a simple open turn at a wall. Prerequisite: Successful completion of Level 3.

event_name: Drawing at the de Young Museum
event_description: This  hands-on workshop invites participants to explore the rich, tactile world of  oil pastels through a series of guided exercises inspired by the vibrant  collections of the de Young Museum. Blending drawing and painting techniques,  participants will learn how to layer, blend, and build texture using oil  pastels to create expressive, colorful works on paper. Participants will  engage with museum artworks as sources of inspiration—drawing connections  between historical and contemporary uses of color, composition, and gesture.  Emphasis will be placed on personal expression, process, and experimentation  rather than representational accuracy, making this workshop accessible to all  skill levels.    At the de Young Museum, sketching is allowed in the permanent collection  with a pencil and a small (9 x 12 inch or smaller) pad. At the first class  the class will meet at the lily pound outside of the de Young. Please do not  be late for the first day of the class as important information and rules  will be covered before going inside the museum. Students are responsible for  their own entry tickets if needed. Please bring drawing materials to class.  See materials list at sharonartstudio.org.

This    after school ceramics program is accessible to all skill levels and offers    the opportunity to try a variety of ceramic techniques. We’ll explore hand    building, throwing on the wheel, surface texture, and glazing. Materials are    included in the price of the class.

Join us    this fall for an Introductory SoulCollage® Workshop, a creative and intuitive    journey into self-discovery. Fall and Winter are seasons where the longer    nights invite us to turn inwards. It’s a naturally creative time where dreams    and imagination can be more accessible. In this workshop, using a simple yet    powerful collage technique, you’ll create 2-3 personal cards that reflect    different supportive aspects of your inner world— strengths, community, and    wisdom. The unique images that we are called to choose and create, can help    guide us, in answering important questions and aligning us more deeply with    our intuition and gifts. No prior art experience is needed; just bring your    curiosity and an open heart. Through guided reflection and sharing, you'll    deepen your connection to yourself and others in a warm, supportive space.    Come explore, create, and uncover the insights waiting to be revealed! All    materials provided.

For    active adults looking for an intermediate to advanced physical conditioning    class that will provide a challenging and intensive low impact workout,    focusing on body strength and flexibility. Discover the serene beauty of San Francisco’s waterways with a self-guided kayaking experience at either Lake Merced or China Basin. Paddle at your own pace as you explore the lake’s tranquil waters, diverse wildlife, and natural habitats—an ideal way to connect with nature and enjoy a refreshing outdoor adventure right in the city. Enrollment includes the rental of a tandem (two-person) kayak and covers up to two participants. Personal flotation devices are provided for all participants. Children 12 and under must be accompanied by an adult in the kayak. All participants must sign a release waiver on the day of their session. Instructional safety videos must be viewed prior to paddling; a link to the videos and waiver will be emailed the week before your scheduled time. Registered participants under the age of 12 must be accompanied on the water by a registered parent or guardian. Expect to get wet—please bring a towel and a change of clothes.

event_name: Jewelry Workshop: Modern Sparkles - Wire Forming & Wrapping
event_description: Join us  for a creative jewelry-making experience where you can design your very own  convertible earrings and pendants! In this class, you’ll craft unique  gemstone compositions using a variety of colorful, semiprecious stones such  as freshwater pearl, chalcedony, apatite, chrysoprase, citrine, quartz, and  more. All materials, including stones, wire, and tools, are provided. We’ll  guide you through wire forming and wrapping techniques to create stunning  earrings and pendants using a cold connection method—no heat or chemicals  required! For the final project, you’ll work with 14k gold-filled wire to  create versatile, ready-to-wear pieces that can be customized to suit your  style. Feel free to bring your own small treasures to incorporate into your  design. Open to all skill levels. Tools and materials are provided. Please  Note: The Jewelry Studio is located on the upper floor, with stair access  only. For accommodations requests or accessibility questions, please contact  rpdaccess@sfgov.org or 415-831-6841.   To help ensure availability, please submit accommodation requests at  least two weeks before the start of the class.

event_name: Adult Swim - Improving Skills and Swimming Strokes
event_description: This class seeks to improve participants' proficiency in basic aquatic skills (including rotary breathing, surface dives and treading) and the six basic swimming strokes (i.e., front crawl, back crawl, butterfly, breaststroke, elementary backstroke and sidestroke). (The butterfly stroke is optional.) Participants also learn skills and concepts needed to stay safe around water, in addition to those needed to help themselves or others in an aquatic emergency.

Participants will receive homework assistance, be exposed to an environment that will promote literacy, encourage communication and empowerment skills while providing recreation activities that include sports, group games, arts and culture, community exploration and seasonal special events. All staff and volunteers receive background checks and are trained in safety skills. Start times may vary based on the school release time. The fee for the school year is $1080. Parents will have the option to pay the entire fee upon registration. Payment plans are available. $270.00 is due upon registration and on the first day of October, January and March of the school year.

event_description: Discover the serene beauty of San Francisco’s waterways with a self-guided kayaking experience at either Lake Merced or China Basin. Paddle at your own pace as you explore the lake’s tranquil waters, diverse wildlife, and natural habitats—an ideal way to connect with nature and enjoy a refreshing outdoor adventure right in the city. Enrollment includes the rental of a tandem (two-person) kayak and covers up to two participants. Personal flotation devices are provided for all participants. Children 12 and under must be accompanied by an adult in the kayak. All participants must sign a release waiver on the day of their session. Instructional safety videos must be viewed prior to paddling; a link to the videos and waiver will be emailed the week before your scheduled time. Registered participants under the age of 12 must be accompanied on the water by a registered parent or guardian. Expect to get wet—please bring a towel and a change of clothes.

event_description: Join us    for a thrilling Halloween-themed archery tournament at the oldest public    archery range in the USA! Test your skills by shooting at both indoor scoring    40cm and 60cm targets, as well as a fun 3D target area. Adult distance is set    at 20 yards, while youth distance is 10 yards. Compete in various bow    categories, including: Olympic Recurve, Barebow Recurve, Traditional,    Compound Unlimited, Compound Bowhunter, and Compound Barebow. Awards will be    given after the event. Participants must bring their own equipment. Please    contact joe.arnaldo@sfgov.org for more information. Deadline to register    10/19/2024.

Paddle at your own pace as you explore the lake’s tranquil waters, diverse wildlife, and natural habitats—an ideal way to connect with nature and enjoy a refreshing outdoor adventure right in the city. Enrollment includes the rental of a tandem (two-person) kayak and covers up to two participants. Personal flotation devices are provided for all participants. Children 12 and under must be accompanied by an adult in the kayak. All participants must sign a release waiver on the day of their session. Instructional safety videos must be viewed prior to paddling; a link to the videos and waiver will be emailed the week before your scheduled time. Registered participants under the age of 12 must be accompanied on the water by a registered parent or guardian. Expect to get wet—please bring a towel and a change of clothes.

The primary purpose of the lifeguard training program is to provide entry-level lifeguard skills and knowledge to prevent, recognize, and respond to emergencies and to provide care for sudden illnesses until advanced medical personnel arrives and takes over. This program includes a lifeguard training course with aquatics-specific first aid and cardio-pulmonary resuscitation (CPR) training. Note: Participants MUST pass the pre-test on the first day of class. The test consists of the following: 300-yard swim; tread water for 2 minute without the use of arms; swim 20 yards, then surface dive to retrieve a 10-lb brick, swim back to the starting point with both hands on the brick, and climb out of the water without assistance, skill must be performed in under 1 minute 40 seconds. Depending on the skills of the participants and their comprehension of the materials presented, the participants may be dismissed early or need to stay later each day.

Discover the serene beauty of San Francisco’s waterways with a self-guided kayaking experience at either Lake Merced or China Basin. Paddle at your own pace as you explore the lake’s tranquil waters, diverse wildlife, and natural habitats—an ideal way to connect with nature and enjoy a refreshing outdoor adventure right in the city. Enrollment includes the rental of a tandem (two-person) kayak and covers up to two participants. Personal flotation devices are provided for all participants. Children 12 and under must be accompanied by an adult in the kayak. All participants must sign a release waiver on the day of their session. Instructional safety videos must be viewed prior to paddling; a link to the videos and waiver will be emailed the week before your scheduled time. Registered participants under the age of 12 must be accompanied on the water by a registered parent or guardian. Expect to get wet—please bring a towel and a change of clothes.

event_name: After School Program - Midtown Terrace Wait List
event_description: **You are adding to the wait list only**The After School program is currently full. You are adding to the wait list for the 2025-26 school year. If a spot opens up and we are able to offer you a spot, we will reach out. This afterschool program only pick up participants from Clarendon.  Our after school program is an experience that provides a safe and nurturing environment for youth in grades K-5 to develop life long recreation and leisure skills. Participants will receive homework assistance, be exposed to an environment that will promote literacy, encourage communication and empowerment skills while providing recreation activities that include sports, group games, arts and culture, community exploration and seasonal special events. All staff and volunteers receive background checks and are trained in safety skills. Start times may vary based on the school release time. The fee for the school year is $1,080. Parents will have the option to pay the entire fee upon registration. Payment plans are available. $270 is due upon registration and on the first day of October, January and March of the school year.

This class builds on the skills learned in Levels 1 and 2. Participants learn to swim the front crawl and elementary backstroke at rudimentary proficiency levels and are introduced to the scissors and dolphin kicks. Participants learn the survival float and increase the time duration for treading water. Participants also learn the rules for headfirst entries and begin to learn to enter the water headfirst from a seated position at poolside (if the water is 9 feet deep or deeper). On successful completion of Level 3, participants have achieved basic water competency in a pool environment. Prerequisite: Successful completion of Level 2. Children must be 48 to participate.  Registration is limited to one swim class per participant.

Las maestras lo guiarán a usted y a sus pequeños a través de actividades que incluyen canciones, bailes, y lecturas divertidas. Para edades de 6–36 meses + cuidador/a. Gratis para inscribirse. Tenga en cuenta: debido a nuestro pequeño tamaño de clase, le pedimos a las familias que se registren solo para las clases a las que puede asistir. Si ya no puede asistir a una clase, cancele su registro o contáctenos en firststeps@fccenters.org. ¡Gracias! Las inscripciones se abrirán el día 28 de cada mes a las 9 de la mañana. • • • First Steps是適合孩子和家長一起學習的遊戲小組。 我們的老師將與您們一起歌曲、舞蹈、閲讀等活動。 免費報名。適合6-36個月的孩子 + 家長/監護人。 請注意：由於我們的班級規模較小，我們要求家庭只註冊您可以參加的課程。 如果您不能再上課，請取消註冊或通過 firststeps@fccenters.org 聯繫我們。 謝謝你! 每月28日上午9:00開始報名。 • • • First Steps là một nhóm trẻ mẫu giáo được giám sát bởi người lớn để các gia đình học tập cùng nhau. Các giáo viên của chúng tôi sẽ hướng dẫn bạn và con bạn thông qua các hoạt động hấp dẫn liên quan đến bài hát, điệu nhảy ngộ nghĩnh. Từ 6-36 tháng tuổi + cha mẹ/người chăm sóc. Ghi danh miễn phí. Xin lưu ý: do quy mô lớp học nhỏ, chúng tôi yêu cầu các gia đình chỉ đăng ký cho các lớp học mà bạn có thể tham dự. Nếu bạn không thể tham gia lớp học được nữa, vui lòng hủy đăng ký hoặc liên hệ với chúng tôi tại firststeps@fccenters.org. Cảm ơn! Cổng đăng ký sẽ mở vào lúc 9:00 sáng ngày 28 hàng tháng.

This class builds on the skills learned in Levels 1 and 2. Participants learn to swim the front crawl and elementary backstroke at rudimentary proficiency levels and are introduced to the scissors and dolphin kicks. Participants learn the survival float and increase the time duration for treading water. Participants also learn the rules for headfirst entries and begin to learn to enter the water headfirst from a seated position at poolside (if the water is 9 feet deep or deeper). On successful completion of Level 3, participants have achieved basic water competency in a pool environment. Prerequisite: Successful completion of Level 2. Children must be 48 to participate.  Registration is limited to one swim class per participant.

Instructional safety videos must be viewed prior to paddling; a link to the videos and waiver will be emailed the week before your scheduled time. Registered participants under the age of 12 must be accompanied on the water by a registered parent or guardian. Expect to get wet—please bring a towel and a change of clothes.

This    class is a playful, low-pressure dive into abstract image-making through hand    printed techniques. Pilates    is a body conditioning routine that seeks to build flexibility, strength,    endurance, and coordination without adding muscle bulk. In addition, Pilates    increases circulation and helps to sculpt the body and strengthen the body's    core or powerhouse (torso). People who do Pilates regularly feel they have    better posture, are less prone to injury, and experience better overall    health.

event_name: Exploring Water Based Media in Abstract Landscapes
event_description: When you  think of water based paints, you might only think of watercolor and maybe  acrylic. But the truth is, there are a wide variety of possibilities  including watercolor pencils, water soluble crayons and pastels, ink, and  more. The diversity of mark making and the changeable nature of those marks  offer much to explore. This is a process based class that prioritizes  experimentation as a way to let go of perfectionism. Only happy accidents  here!    We will do several quick studies and then use our favorite ideas and  techniques to make a large work on 350 weight cold press paper. All materials  provided.

Discover the serene beauty of San Francisco’s waterways with a self-guided kayaking experience at either Lake Merced or China Basin. Paddle at your own pace as you explore the lake’s tranquil waters, diverse wildlife, and natural habitats—an ideal way to connect with nature and enjoy a refreshing outdoor adventure right in the city. Enrollment includes the rental of a tandem (two-person) kayak and covers up to two participants. Personal flotation devices are provided for all participants. Children 12 and under must be accompanied by an adult in the kayak. All participants must sign a release waiver on the day of their session. Instructional safety videos must be viewed prior to paddling; a link to the videos and waiver will be emailed the week before your scheduled time. Registered participants under the age of 12 must be accompanied on the water by a registered parent or guardian. Expect to get wet—please bring a towel and a change of clothes.

There is much more in Hatha yoga practice than poses. In this series, we still explore practices aimed to improve our physical well-being through asanas (poses); we also introduce practices that include pranayama (breath expansion) techniques, and finally we experience the benefits of simple meditation techniques. The intention is awareness at a physical, mental and emotional level on as well as off the mat.

event_name: Figure Drawing I: Learning by Hand
event_description: Figure    drawing is an active process; an engagement with material that is both    physical and intellectual. In this class, students will be encouraged to work    in terms of process rather than making a finished product, in order to foster    curiosity and therefore, insight. Insights will be learned through visual    problem solving, exploring the looking and seeing relationship, and the    expression of touching marker to paper. This class will take full advantage    of its in class time for drawing time, with instruction limited to demos and    corrections. Each class will have a particular focus on the figure and    helpful techniques for rendering. Price of the model is included in the cost    of the class. Please bring paper and drawing materials to class. Materials    list available at sharonartstudio.org.
